Data looks leptokurtic. Might not be as useful as I thought it might.

Determine cutoffs for exponential growth

Kale continues growing throughout the season, but beans and oats both stop growing after a few weeks. I think it is reasonable to just “eyeball” the point at which they stop growing, and look at growth rates before that point (the alternative would be a logistic or changepoint model—logistic might be worth looking into).

Beans

## Warning: Removed 689 rows containing non-finite values (stat_summary).

Oats

## Warning: Removed 816 rows containing non-finite values (stat_summary).

Less clear for oats—it seems like the end of growth depends on the treatment with oats in current dry conditions not really leveling off in size until the very end and in current ambient conditions growth is leveling off by 8/07.
